title.narrative: Country Health Information Systems and Data Use (CHISU)

description.narrative: (Burkina Faso): Through this mechanism USAID will support the Directorate General of Studies and Statistics and the Directorate of Information Systems in the Ministry of Health (MoH) to:.Strengthen collection, analysis, and use of routine health data by supporting the Ministry of Health in the data selection, collection, and processing of routine health information, and to streamline and improve data collection, storage, and analysis of data for decision making..Improve country-level capacity to manage health information systems and resources by supporting systems across health areas at all levels of the health system in strategic planning and governance of the National Health Information System. .Improve and apply methods, tools, and approaches to address health information challenges and gaps by increasing the local use, analysis, communication, and ownership of data..Support interoperability between the electronic logistics management information, the health management information system, and the community-based digitization system. .This activity will contribute to the U.S. Embassy Ouagadougou's Integrated Country Strategy, specifically Mission Goal 3.2 Improve the health and nutrition of the people of Burkina Faso by investing in people and institutional capacity. This activity contributes to the Journey to Self-Reliance by promoting greater commitment and strengthening the capacity of the Burkina Faso MoH. The interventions will reinforce the health system through the 2021-2025 Health Information System Strategic Plan. .
